  "prompt": "Could CAT exam and MAT exam take place on same day (4th December 2016)?",
  "response": "No, the CAT (Common Admission Test) and MAT (Management Aptitude Test) exams are typically scheduled on different dates to avoid any conflict for candidates who might want to appear for both exams. The CAT exam is generally conducted by the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) and takes place on a predetermined Sunday in November or December. On the other hand, the MAT exam is conducted by the All India Management Association (AIMA) and is held multiple times a year, including December. However, AIMA usually ensures that MAT dates do not clash with other major management entrance exams like CAT. Therefore, it is unlikely that both exams would take place on the same day, such as December 4, 2016.",
